<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>Upgrading your AR15 can enhance not only its functionality but also your shooting experience. In this guide, we focus on the installation of the BCM Gunfighter KAG (Kinesthetic Angled Grip), a hand stop that adds versatility to your rifle setup. Let's walk through how to effectively install this accessory to improve your grip and control while shooting.</p>

<h2>What This Video Demonstrates</h2>
<p>This video offers a step-by-step guide to installing the BCM Gunfighter KAG on an AR15 equipped with an M-LOK handguard. The KAG is designed for positive hand placement, granting users the ability to index their hands consistently while also providing additional control over the rifle. With its low-profile design, it minimizes bulk while maximizing function, making it an excellent choice for AR constructions.</p>

<h2>Step-by-Step Explanation</h2>
<p>The first step in our installation involves the preparation of the AR15's handguard, specifically the M-LOK slots where the KAG will be attached. M-LOK is known for its ease of use and secure fittings, which makes the installation process straightforward.</p>
<p>1. **Positioning the KAG**: Determine where you wish to place the KAG on the handguard. The recommended spot allows for a comfortable grip while shooting and can be adjusted based on your shooting style.</p>
<p>2. **Inserting the KAG**: Slot the KAG into the M-LOK rail and ensure it is aligned properly. The installation involves a cam mechanism that secures the grip firmly as you tighten it.</p>
<p>3. **Tightening the Grip**: Using the included allen wrench, tighten down the KAG. It’s important to ensure it’s secure but avoid over-tightening, which could damage the accessories. A small amount of thread lock is included to prevent loosening over time.</p>
<p>4. **Testing the Installation**: Once installed, check for stability and positioning. The grip should feel natural and offer a solid point for your hand to maintain control of the weapon. It should also provide versatility for various shooting positions, including a dynamic c-clamp method.</p>

<h2>Key Tips</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Place the KAG where it feels most comfortable for your shooting style; you might want to experiment with different positions while at the range.</li>
    <li>When tightening the KAG, keep it finger-tight to allow for future adjustments without hassle.</li>
    <li>Familiarize yourself with the functionality of the KAG in a controlled environment to ensure it complements your shooting technique.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
<p>The BCM Gunfighter KAG is an effective addition to an AR15 build that enhances grip stability and control. Its installation is user-friendly and adaptable, making it a great choice for any shooter looking to improve their rifle handling. Whether you are utilizing it for competitive shooting or personal defense, this upgrade can make a substantial difference in your shooting experience.</p>

